01905256/|title=Ken Loach\u2019s \u2018I, Daniel Blake\u2019 Leads British Independent Film Awards Race|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Leo|last=Barraclough|date=November 1, 2016|accessdate=November 8, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/i-daniel-blake-hayley-squires-british-independent-film-awards-1201933357/|title=Sasha Lane Wins for \u2018American Honey\u2019 at British Independent Film Awards|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Leo|last=Barraclough|date=December 4, 2016|accessdate=December 4, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2016\n| Indiana Film Journalist Association Awards\n| Best Actress\n| ''American Honey''\n| {{Nominated}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianafilmjournalists.com/index|title=2016 IFJA Film Awards Nominations - Indiana Film Journalists Association|author=|date=|website=indianafilmjournalists.com|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2016\n| Indiana Film Journalist Association Awards\n| Breakout of the Year\n| ''American Honey''\n| {{draw|Runner-up}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianafilmjournalists.com/|title=Indiana Film Journalists Association|author=|date=|website=indianafilmjournalists.com|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[32nd Independent Spirit Awards|2017]]\n| [[Independent Spirit Awards]]\n| [[Independent Spirit Award for Best Female Lead|Best Female Lead]]\n| ''American Honey''\n| {{Nominated}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmindependent.org/blog/film-independent-spirit-awards-nominations-announced/|title=2017 Film Independent Spirit Awards Nominations Announced!|last=Warren|first=Matt|date=November 22, 2016|publisher=[[Independent Spirit Awards]]|accessdate=November 22, 2016}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|7603745}}\n* {{rotten-tomatoes-person|sasha_lane}}\n\n{{BIFA Award for Best Performance by an Actress in a British Independent Film}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lane, Sasha}}\n[[Category:1995 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Dallas]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Houston]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:African-American actresses]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American people of M\u0101ori descent]]\n[[Category:American people of New Zealand descent]]\n[[Category:Lesbian actresses]]\n[[Category:LGBT African Americans]]\n[[Category:LGBT entertainers from the United States]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Texas]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Frisco, Texas]]\n[[Category:Texas State University alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name         = Sasha Lane\n| image        = Sasha Lane (29669508886).jpg\n| caption      = Lane in Toronto, 2016\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1995|9|29}}\n| birth_place  = [[Houston, Texas]], U.S.\n| birth_name   = Sasha Bianca Lane\n| occupation   = Actress\n| years_active = 2016\u2013present\n| relatives    = \n| residence    = [[Los Angeles, California]], U.S.\n}}\n'''Sasha Bianca Lane''' (born September 29, 1995)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://search.ancestry.com/cgi-bin/sse.dll?db=TXbirthindex&gss=sfs28_ms_db&new=1&rank=1&msT=1&gsfn=Sasha&gsfn_x=0&msbdd=29&msbdd_x=1&msbdm=9&msbdm_x=1&msbdy=1995&msbdy_x=1&_83004003-n_xcl=m&MSAV=0&uidh=000|title=Texas Birth Index, 1903-1997|website=ancestry.com|accessdate=August 22, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"wonderland\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wonderlandmagazine.com/2016/05/stars-aligned-sasha/|title=Stars Aligned: Sasha|website=Wonderland Magazine|date=May 31, 2016|accessdate=June 1, 2016}}</ref> is an American actress. She made her film debut in ''[[American Honey (film)|American Honey]]'' (2016) directed by [[Andrea Arnold]].\n\n==Early life==\nLane was born in [[Houston, Texas]], and grew up in [[Dallas, Texas]]. Her father is [[African Americans|African-American]], and her mother, who is from [[New Zealand]], is of [[M\u0101ori people|M\u0101ori]] descent.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/esmagazine/meet-the-fashions-new-muses-a3468276.html|title=Meet fashion's new muses|last=Dacre|first=Karen|date=February 16, 2017|access-date=February 18, 2017|work=[[London Evening Standard]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.glamour.com/story/american-honey-actress-sasha-lane|title=American Honey Actress Sasha Lane's Incredible Story About How She Was Discovered on Spring Break|last=Branch|first=Kate|date=September 29, 2016|access-date=February 18, 2017|work=[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]]}}</ref> After her parents divorced when she was young, Lane went to live with her mother, moving several times near [[Dallas]] before settling in [[Frisco, Texas]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2016/oct/13/american-honeys-sasha-lane-im-exhausted-by-people-i-want-to-be-alone-so-bad|title=American Honey's Sasha Lane: 'I\u2019m exhausted by people \u2014 I want to be alone so bad'|last=Iqbal|first=Nosheen|date=October 13, 2016|access-date=February 18, 2017|work=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref> Prior to becoming an actress, Lane worked as a waitress at a restaurant in Frisco, and was also a stand-out athlete on basketball, track, and field teams.{{cn|date=March 2020}} She attended [[Texas State University]] in [[San Marcos, Texas]], but left.<ref name=\"wonderland\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theblondesalad.com/2016/05/woman-crush-wednesday-sasha-lane.html|title=WOMAN CRUSH WEDNESDAY: SASHA LANE|website=The Blond Salad|first=Vincenzo|last=Malinconcio|date=May 18, 2016|accessdate=June 1, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nLane made her film debut in the critically acclaimed and award-winning ''[[American Honey (film)|American Honey]]'' (2016), a film about magazine crews, written and directed by [[Andrea Arnold]], starring opposite [[Shia LaBeouf]] and [[Riley Keough]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ethiogrio.com/news/world-news/32766-how-sasha-lane-won-hollywood-role-in-american-honey-and-bagged-shia-labeouf.html|title=How Sasha Lane won Hollywood role in American Honey and bagged Shia LaBeouf|website=Ethiogrio|first=Jasmine|last=Wright|date=September 23, 2015|accessdate=May 16, 2016}}</ref> Arnold spotted Lane sunbathing on a beach while on spring break. Lane said in an interview that she \"felt Arnold's vibe and decided to trust Arnold for an audition.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanityfair.com/style/2016/05/sasha-lane-barefoot-cannes-julia-roberts|title=Julia Roberts Inspires More Stars to Go Barefoot at Cannes|website=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]|first=Lauren|last=Le Vine|date=May 16, 2016|accessdate=May 16, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2016/may/15/andrea-arnold-in-cannes-i-was-shocked-and-upset-by-the-poverty-i-saw-in-the-us|title=Andrea Arnold in Cannes: I was shocked and upset by the poverty I saw in the US|website=[[The Guardian]]|first=Catherine|last=Shoard|date=May 15, 2016|accessdate=May 16, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/andrea-arnold-making-american-honey-cannes-press-conference|title=Cannes: Andrea Arnold on the 'Difficult Times' Making 'American Honey' on the Road in the U.S.|website=[[Indiewire.com]]|first=Graham|last=Winfrey|date=May 15, 2016|accessdate=May 16, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe film had its world premiere on May 15, 2016 at the [[Cannes Film Festival]], where it won the [[Jury Prize (Cannes Film Festival)|Prix du Jury]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2016/film/festivals/cannes-film-festival-official-selection-lineup-2016-1201753269/ |title=Cannes 2016: Film Festival Unveils Official Selection Lineup |accessdate=14 April 2016 |work=Variety}}</ref> The film was released in a [[limited release]] on September 30, 2016, by [[A24 (company)|A24]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://deadline.com/2016/01/american-honey-movie-a24-shia-labeouf-andrea-arnold-sasha-lane-1201686302/ |title=Andrea Arnold\u2019s \u2018American Honey\u2019 Attracts A24 |publisher=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |first=Patrick |last=Hipes |date=January 19, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/06/american-honey-moonlight-a24-release-dates-1201780991/|title=A24 Sets Dates For \u2018Moonlight\u2019 & Cannes Jury Prize Winner \u2018American Honey\u2019|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|date=June 28, 2016|accessdate=November 7, 2016}}</ref> In 2017, Lane starred in ''Born in the Maelstrom'', a short film directed by Meryam Joobeur,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.interviewmagazine.com/film/sasha-lane|title=Sasha Lane: Star Rising|website=[[Interview Magazine]]|first=Colleen|last=Kelsey|date=September 30, 2016|accessdate=November 7, 2016}}</ref> In 2018, Lane starred in ''[[Hearts Beat Loud]]'', opposite [[Nick Offerman]] and [[Kiersey Clemons]], directed by [[Brett Haley]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/nick-offerman-hearts-beat-loud-1202508642/|title=Nick Offerman to Star in Music Drama \u2018Hearts Beat Loud\u2019 With Kiersey Clemons|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Dave|last=McNary|date=July 27, 2017|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref> and ''[[The Miseducation of Cameron Post (film)|The Miseducation of Cameron Post]]'' directed by [[Desiree Akhavan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/chloe-grace-moretz-sasha-lane-star-gay-conversion-drama-miseducation-cameron-post-948742|title=Chloe Grace Moretz, Sasha Lane to Star in Gay Conversion Drama 'The Miseducation of Cameron Post|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|first=Tatiana|last=Siegel|date=November 18, 2016|accessdate=November 18, 2016}}</ref> ''The Miseducation of Cameron Post'' won Top Prize at the [[2018 Sundance Film Festival]] and has been praised for its \u201csensitive, understated portrayal of adolescent self-doubt and discovery.\u201d <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/sasha-lane-young-hollywood-2018|title=Sasha Lane Is Ready to Aim Her Punches at Hollywood|last=Nast|first=Cond\u00e9|website=Teen Vogue|language=en|access-date=2019-01-28}}</ref> In 2019, Lane played Alice Monaghan in ''[[Hellboy (2019 film)|Hellboy]]'', directed by [[Neil Marshall]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/hellboy-reboot-adds-sasha-lane-1027514|title=Hellboy' Reboot Adds 'American Honey' Star Sasha Lane (Exclusive)|website=The Hollywood Reporter|first=Rebecca|last=Ford|date=August 15, 2017|accessdate=July 30, 2018}}</ref> \n\nShe appeared in horror thriller film ''[[Daniel Isn't Real]]'' (2019), directed by Adam Egypt Mortimer.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/patrick-schwarzenegger-sasha-lane-join-thriller-daniel-isnt-real-1129518|title=Patrick Schwarzenegger, Sasha Lane Join Thriller 'Daniel Isn't Real'|website=The Hollywood Reporter|first=Etan|last=Vlessing|date=July 24, 2018|accessdate=July 24, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nWhile promoting her 2018 film ''[[The Miseducation of Cameron Post (film)|The Miseducation of Cameron Post]]'' during the Sundance Film Festival press junket, Lane stated she is gay.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiewire.com/2018/01/sasha-lane-comes-out-gay-lesbian-lgbt-1201920547/|title=Sasha Lane Discusses Her Gay Identity in \u2018The Miseducation of Cameron Post\u2019 \u2014 Sundance 2018|first=Jude|last=Dry|date=22 January 2018|website=indiewire.com|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref> She had previously called herself [[bisexual]].<ref>{{cite tweet|user=SashaBianca23|author=Sasha Lane|number=562404191096684544|date=3 February 2015|title=I feel like people keep trynna include me in they threesomes bc I'm bi and they think ill do all the work and it'll make their bf amused}}</ref> As of 2016, she lives in [[Los Angeles]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" | Director\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 2016\n| ''[[American Honey (film)|American Honey]]''\n| Star\n| {{sortname|Andrea|Arnold}}\n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 2017\n| ''Born in the Maelstrom''\n| Rebecca\n| {{sort|Joobeur|Meryam Joobeur}}\n| Short film\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 2018\n| ''{{sort|Miseducation of Cameron Post|[[The Miseducation of Cameron Post (film)|The Miseducation of Cameron Post]]}}''\n| {{sort|Fonda|[[Jane Fonda]]}}\n| {{sortname|Desiree|Akhavan}}\n|\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 2018\n| ''[[Hearts Beat Loud]]''\n| Rose\n| {{sortname|Brett|Haley}}\n|\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 2018\n| ''[[Shrimp (film)|Shrimp]]''\n| Dominatrix\n| {{sortname|Zelda|Williams}}\n| Short film\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 2018\n| ''[[After Everything]]''\n| Lindsay\n| {{sortname|Hannah|Marks}}<br>Joey Power\n|\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 2019\n| ''[[Daniel Isn't Real]]''\n| Cassie\n| {{sort|Mortimer|Adam Egypt Mortimer}}\n|\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 2019\n| ''[[Hellboy (2019 film)|Hellboy]]''\n| {{sort|Monaghan|Alice Monaghan}}\n| {{sortname|Neil|Marshall}}\n|\n|-\n|}\n<!-- Per WP:NFF and WP:CRYSTAL, do not add films that are listed as \"pre-production\" -->\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n|2020\n| scope=\"row\"| ''[[Amazing Stories (2020 TV series)|Amazing Stories]]''\n| Alia\n| Episode: \"Signs of Life\"\n|-\n|2020\n| scope=\"row\" | ''[[Utopia (2020 TV series)|Utopia]]''\n| Jessica Hyde\n| Upcoming series\n|-\n|2021\n| ''[[Loki (TV series)|Loki]]''\n| TBA\n| Upcoming series\n|}\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Association\n! Category\n! Nominated work\n! Result\n! {{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n| [[Gotham Independent Film Awards 2016|2016]]\n| [[Gotham Awards]]\n| [[Gotham Independent Film Award for Breakthrough Actor|Breakthrough Actor]]\n| ''American Honey''\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/gotham-awards-nominations-2016-list-nominees-1201895205/?platform=hootsuite|title=Gotham Awards Nominations 2016: \u2018Manchester By The Sea\u2019 Leads with Four|last=Cox|first=Gordon|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=November 8, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[British Independent Film Awards 2016|2016]]\n| [[British Independent Film Awards]] \n| [[BIFA Award for Best Performance by an Actress in a British Independent Film|Best Performance by an Actress in a British Independent Film]]\n| ''American Honey''\n| {{won}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/global/ken-loach-i-daniel-blake-british-independent-film-awards-1201905256/|title=Ken Loach\u2019s \u2018I, Daniel Blake\u2019 Leads British Independent Film Awards Race|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Leo|last=Barraclough|date=November 1, 2016|accessdate=November 8, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/i-daniel-blake-hayley-squires-british-independent-film-awards-1201933357/|title=Sasha Lane Wins for \u2018American Honey\u2019 at British Independent Film Awards|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Leo|last=Barraclough|date=December 4, 2016|accessdate=December 4, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2016\n| Indiana Film Journalist Association Awards\n| Best Actress\n| ''American Honey''\n| {{Nominated}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianafilmjournalists.com/index|title=2016 IFJA Film Awards Nominations - Indiana Film Journalists Association|author=|date=|website=indianafilmjournalists.com|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2016\n| Indiana Film Journalist Association Awards\n| Breakout of the Year\n| ''American Honey''\n| {{draw|Runner-up}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianafilmjournalists.com/|title=Indiana Film Journalists Association|author=|date=|website=indianafilmjournalists.com|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[32nd Independent Spirit Awards|2017]]\n| [[Independent Spirit Awards]]\n| [[Independent Spirit Award for Best Female Lead|Best Female Lead]]\n| ''American Honey''\n| {{Nominated}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmindependent.org/blog/film-independent-spirit-awards-nominations-announced/|title=2017 Film Independent Spirit Awards Nominations Announced!|last=Warren|first=Matt|date=November 22, 2016|publisher=[[Independent Spirit Awards]]|accessdate=November 22, 2016}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|7603745}}\n* {{rotten-tomatoes-person|sasha_lane}}\n\n{{BIFA Award for Best Performance by an Actress in a British Independent Film}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lane, Sasha}}\n[[Category:1995 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Dallas]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Houston]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:African-American actresses]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American people of M\u0101ori descent]]\n[[Category:American people of New Zealand descent]]\n[[Category:Lesbian actresses]]\n[[Category:LGBT African Americans]]\n[[Category:LGBT entertainers from the United States]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Texas]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Frisco, Texas]]\n[[Category:Texas State University alumni]]\n", "name_user": "189.122.22.251", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200ePersonal life)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sasha_Lane"}
{"title_page": "Siddharth Kannan", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Like resume|date=August 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name\t\t= Siddharth Kannan\n| image\t\t=\n| image_size    = \n| birth_place\t= [[New Delhi]], [[India]]\n| nationality\t= [[India]]n\n| spouse        = Neha Kannan (2 Feb 2014)\n| height\t= 6ft 2 inch (186 cms)\n| occupation\t= TV and radio host, announcer, [[voice-over]] actor, film critic<ref>{{cite news|url=http://bollyspice.com/71879/bullett-raja-gets-impressive-4-5-stars-several-top-critics|title=Bullett Raja gets an impressive 4 out of 5 stars from several top critics |date=1 December 2013|accessdate=16 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dhanrajfilms.co.in/reviews.html|title=Ankur Arora Murder Case Scores High on Critic Reviews|accessdate=16 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://twitter.com/bwooduncensored/status/426697207828324353|title=Bollywood Uncensored|accessdate=16 April 2015}}</ref>\n| years_active\t= 1994-present\n| website       ={{url|www.siddharthkannan.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Siddharth Kannan''' is an Indian television and radio host, announcer, [[voice-over]] actor and a film critic.\n\n==Early life and background==\n\nHe was born in New Delhi to parents V.Kannan and Radha Kannan, Sid K as he is popularly known as, moved to [[Kolkata]] with them and then spent 8 years in Lucknow and finally moved base with his family to Mumbai in 1994.\n\n==Career==\n\n===Radio===\n\nAt the age of 14, Siddharth joined Times FM as a Radio Host. He holds the record for becoming the youngest radio host in India.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://entertainment.gaeatimes.com/2009/05/ran03/siddharth-kannan-returns-to-his-first-love-1432/ |title= Siddharth Kannan returns to his first love|date=3 May 2009|accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref>  In 1997, while at college, he joined Radio Star on 107.1 FM and hosted a show with Cyrus Broacha called \u2018Miranda Char Baje Band Baje\u2019. He started India\u2019s first radio school called \u2018Wild on Air\u2019 in 1999. Emirates 2 FM in Dubai syndicated their Hindi shows to him, for whom he hosted and produced shows from Mumbai.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://hamaraphotos.com/siddharth_kannan_3109.html |title=Siddharth Kannan |accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref> He also produced and hosted shows for Rediff Radio on rediff.com. In 2009,He started an A list Bollywood  celebrity chat show \u2018Meow Starburst\u2019 on Meow 104.8fm.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Siddharth-Kannan-on-a-roll/articleshow/45249126.cms  |title=Siddharth Kannan on a roll |date=24 Nov 2014|accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref> Later called as \u2018Oye talkies\u2019 and then re-christened as \u2018Bollywood Khul Ke \u2018 on Oye 104.8FM(a TV Today Network initiative).<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.afaqs.com/media/media_newslets/?id=55345_I+am+scared+of+Salman+Khan!-Karan+Johar+reveals+to+Sid+K+on+Oye+104.8+FM|title='I am scared of Salman Khan!'-Karan Johar reveals to Sid K on Oye 104.8 FM|date=29 Oct 2012|accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.indiainfoline.com/article/news-business/salman-khan-discloses-only-on-oye-104-8-fm-113110105923_1.html|title=Salman Khan discloses only on Oye 104.8 FM!|date=16 Aug 2012|accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.santabanta.com/bollywood/58867/bipasha-reveals-shes-in-love-with-brad/|title=\nBipasha reveals she's in love with 'Brad'|date=7 September 2012|accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref> Sid K has interviewed Amitabh Bachchan, Shahrukh Khan, Salman Khan, Himesh Reshammiya, Aamir Khan, Ranbir Kapoor, Deepika Padukone, and Katrina Kaif.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.getmovieinfo.com/pantaloons-unveil-bang-bang-collection-hrithik-roshan-katrina-kaif/07-hrithik-roshan-katrina-kaif-with-siddharth-kannan-shaking-their-legslaunch-of-bang-bang-inspired-pantaloons-collection/|title= Hrithik Roshan & Katrina Kaif with Siddharth Kannan shaking their legs@launch of Bang Bang inspired Pantaloons Collection|accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== Television ===\n\nHe hosted his first TV show in 2006 \u2013\u2019Santa and Banta Newz Unlimited\u2019 with renowned singer and rapper Baba Sehgal on Zoom.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.indiantelevision.org.in/release/y2k7/june/junerel54.php|title=Himesh Reshmmiya on the 50th episode of Santa & Banta Newz Unlimited on Zoom|date=25 June 2007|accessdate=3 April 2015}}</ref> In 2010,Sid started his next TV show \u2018See Taare Mastiii Mein\u2019 \u2013An \u2018A list\u2019 celebrity chat show on Mastiii.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/entertainment/siddharth-kannan-is-back-on-television_100442974.html|title=Siddharth Kannan is back on Television|date=10 Dec 2010|accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.hamaraphotos.com/most_viewed_bollywood_photos_-_siddharth_kannan_topn_-3109_321.html |title=Salman Khan, Siddharth Kannan at IIFA Press meet to announce Chillar Film and Environment initiatives in Taj Land's End |date=5 June 2011|accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.eventfaqs.com/ec/siddharthkannan |title= Siddharth Kannan |accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref>  In 2012,he was the commentator on \u2018Ring Ka King\u2019 on Colors produced by Endomol India and backed by Total NonStop Action Wrestling (TNA).<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.filmitown.com/2012/01/18/rj-cum-tv-host-siddharth-kannan-as-the-commentator-for-ring-ka-king/ |title=RJ cum TV host Siddharth Kannan as the commentator for \u2018Ring Ka King\u2019 |date=18 Jan 2012|accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://tc02.tellychakkar.com/tv/tv-news/siddharth-kannan-do-commentary-ring-ka-king-go-air-28-january |title=Siddharth Kannan to do commentary in Ring Ka King; to go on air from 28 January|date=20 Jan 2012|accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.filmyfriday.com/television/siddharth-kannan-is-back-on-television |title=Siddharth Kannan is back on Television |accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref> In 2014,he was one of the hosts of Star Sports Pro Kabaddi and in the same year he was the host of the inaugural season of the Champions Tennis League on Sony Six.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.newstrackindia.com/newsdetails/2014/9/17/4-Bigg-Boss-8-Siddharth-Kannan-offered-Big-Boss.html  |title=Bigg Boss 8:Siddharth Kannan offered Big Boss|accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.theindianews24.com/when-siddharth-kannan-challenged-tiger-shroff/ |title=When Siddharth Kannan Challenged Tiger Shroff |accessdate=13 February 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 May 2017, Siddharth Kannan was the official [[red carpet]] host of the [[Justin Bieber]] concert at [[DY Patil Stadium]], [[Mumbai]].<ref>{{cite web|title=\nJacqueline wants to teach Justin Bieber Bollywood dance! IndiaGlitz|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/jacqueline-fernandes-has-crush-on-justin-bieber-hindi-news-185272.html|work=IndiaGlitz|accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\nDo you know who will host the Red Carpet for the Justin Bieber concert?|url=http://www.radioandmusic.com/entertainment/editorial/news/170510-do-you-know-who-will-host-the-red-carpet-the|work=RadioandMusic|accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Voice Overs==\nHe has been the voice over artist for the IIFA AWARDS (2000-2014), Filmfare Awards and Stardust Awards.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/a-voice-for-all-stages/article1105498.ece |title=A voice for all stages|date=9 Feb 2011|accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#B0C4DE\" align=\"center\"\n! Year !! Shows  \n|-\n| 2000-2004 || ''IIFA AWARDS ''  \n|-\n| 2008 || ''Ford Super Model India'' \n|-\n| 2011 || ''Femina Miss India South'' \n|-\n| 2012 || '' IIFA Weekend Singapore amongst others.''  \n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[Femina Miss India Delhi]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://photogallery.indiatimes.com/beauty-pageants/miss-india/ponds-femina-miss-india-delhi-2013/Ponds-Femina-Miss-India-Delhi-2013-Finale/articleshow/18007769.cms|title=Pond's Femina Miss India, Delhi 2013|accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref>''  \n|-\n| 2014 || ''IIFA World Premiere (Tampa bay)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1140427/jsp/t2/story_18282242.jsp#.VR-mpo4f7IU|title=Do the Tampa|date=27 April 2014|accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref>'' \n|-\n| 2014 || ''IIFA Stomp (Tampa Bay,Usa)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://camerasport.photoshelter.com/image/I0000VBRx0mZIYUI|title=SIDDHARTH KANNAN fires up the crowd at STOMP|date=23 April 2014|accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref>''  \n|-\n| 2014 || ''Provogue Men\u2019s Xp Mr.India World'' \n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[Filmfare Awards]]'' \n|-\n| 2014 || ''Avengers-Age of Ultron (official Hindi trailer)''  \n|-\n| 2014 || ''Spectre (official Hindi trailer-James Bond film)''\n|-\n| 2015 || ''Gima Awards''\n|-\n|2016 || ''Renault Star Guild Awards''\n|}\n\n==Personal life==\n\nSid K\u2019s parents are retired Corporate executives. His elder brother Hrishikesh Kannan, also known as Hrishi K,is a radio host and voice over artist in India.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newswala.com/Entertainment-News/Ace-TV-and-Radio-Host-Siddharth-Kannan-finds-his-Soul-Mate-Neha-Agarwal-54009.html  |title=Ace TV and Radio Host Siddharth Kannan finds his Soul Mate Neha Agarwal!! |accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.dailymotion.com/video/x1b7oax_siddharth-kannan-neha-agarwal-wedding-reception-anil-kapoor-vivek-oberoy_shortfilms |title= Siddharth Kannan & Neha Agarwal Wedding Reception|accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://photogallery.indiatimes.com/events/mumbai/siddharth-kannans-bday-bash/Monisha-Khatwani/articleshow/7842586.cms |title=Siddharth Kannan's b'day bash |date=31 March 2011|accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref>  Siddharth married Neha in 2014 in Chennai and Mumbai.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-pix-anil-kapoor-vivek-at-siddharth-kannans-wedding-reception/20140205.htm  |title=PIX: Anil Kapoor, Vivek at Siddharth Kannan's wedding reception |date=5 Feb 2014|accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://timescity.com/mumbai/party-pics/siddharth-kannans-party/5745837.cms|title= Siddharth Kannan's party, Mumbai TimesCity |accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.sify.com/movies/anil-kapoor-vivek-oberoi-and-other-stars-at-siddharth-kannan-s-wedding-imagegallery-bollywood-ocgrRAehhhcsi.html|title=Anil Kapoor, Vivek Oberoi and other stars at Siddharth Kannan's wedding |accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://ibnlive.in.com/photogallery/15241.html|title=Siddharth Kannan and Neha Agarwal's star-studded wedding reception |date=5 Feb 2014|accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/events/mumbai/Siddharths-starry-wedding/articleshow/29906309.cms|title=Anil Kapoor, Sonu Sood, Shaan at Siddharth Kannan-Neha Agarwal wedding bash in Mumbai|date=6 February 2014|accessdate=31 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.co.in/celebs-at-siddharth-kannans-reception/|title= Siddharth Kannan|accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n==TV shows==\n\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#B0C4DE\" align=\"center\"\n! Year !! Shows  \n|-\n| 2006 || ''Santa and Banta Newz Unlimited on [[Zoom (Indian TV channel)|Zoom]]''  \n|-\n| 2008 || ''Planet Bollywood on [[Zoom (Indian TV channel)|Zoom]]'' \n|-\n| 2010 || ''See Taare Mastiii Mein on Mastiii'' \n|-\n| 2012 || ''Ring Ka King on [[Colors (TV channel)|Colors]]''  \n|-\n| 2014 || ''Star Sports Pro Kabaddi on [[Star